cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the problem of 3D face reconstruction from monocular images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel multi-frame consistency loss, which involves training a deep network, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper uses video clips collected from the Internet, which could fall under the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also deals with the problem of depth ambiguity, which could be related to the cs.GR (Graphics) category. Finally, the paper proposes a highly general 3D face model, which could be related to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
